The paper discusses a novel framework for image classification that uses meta-reasoning and meta-operations to unify predictions into abstractions, properties, or relationships. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of the framework in live video images, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-categories of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
